This paper discusses a recent master's degree proposal which has as its purpose the retraining of teachers from any discipline to teach applied computer science at the community college level. The paper details the curriculum for the program; it discusses the strengths and weaknesses of the program; and it provides information concerning the difficulties in getting the proposal accepted by the ISU Applied Computer Science Department. The proposal has been accepted by both the Applied Computer Science Department and the College Curriculum Committee, and it is now being reviewed by higher university committees. The proposed implementation date is September 1986.